<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Condemns Killings in Algeria </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2303132694 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1300 
GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2303132694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Francois Mitterrand, Prime Minister Edouard 
Balladur, Foreign Minister Alain Juppe, and Defense Minister 
Francois Leotard gathered this morning at the Elysee to discuss 
the situation in Algeria, where two French nationals were killed 
last night. 
  Shortly afterward, the French Foreign Ministry advised those 
French nationals whose presence is not vital in Algeria to leave 
the country. Foreign Ministry spokesman Richard Duque spoke to 
Frederic Barrere: 
  [Begin Duque recording] France condemns the cowardly killing 
of two of its nationals in Algeria--Mr. Roger Drouaier and his 
son Pascal. It denounces this act of barbarity, which marks a 
new phase in violence, thus threatening the presence of 
foreigners on Algerian territory. In this context, it is 
advisable for our nationals whose presence is not vital to take 
the necessary steps to return to France. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

