<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Advises Nationals To Leave Algeria </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2303210394 Madrid TVE Internacional Television in Spanish 
2000 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2303210394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid TVE Internacional Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Spanish Government advises all Spaniards 
residing in Algeria whose presence there is not essential to 
leave the country. The on-going attacks of foreigners by Islamic 
groups are the reason for this warning. The Spanish colony in 
Algeria numbers 327. The advice also covers diplomatic 
personnel whose protection has been increased over the last 
months. 
  The French authorities have also made a similar appeal to 
their community in Algeria. Yesterday's stabbing of a French 
businessman and his son in Algiers means that 31 foreigners have 
been murdered in Algeria over the last six months. 

</TEXT>

