<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on Peacekeeping Participation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2303121294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2303121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Turkey's participation in the peace force in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina registers it in the international arena as a 
country that contributes effectively to the installation of 
peace and stability in the region. 
  In his weekly news conference, Foreign Ministry acting 
spokesman Ferhat Ataman said that now that Turkey is joining the 
peace force in Bosnia-Herzegovina, it will be able to contribute 
more effectively to the establishment and protection of peace 
and stability in the region. Turkey also directly participates 
in activities such as the implementation of the UN no-fly zone 
in the region, Ataman recalled, adding that these efforts will 
continue in the future as well. 

