<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry: Yeoryiadhis Killing `Ridiculous' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2303190894 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1530 GMT 23 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2303190894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Turkish Foreign Ministry has described as 
ridiculous claims by Greek Cypriot authorities on the killing of 
Theofilos Yeoryiadhis, member of the Committee for Solidarity 
with the illegal PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] organization. 
  Speaking at his weekly news conference today, Foreign 
Ministry deputy spokesman Ferhat Ataman said that the accusatory 
language used in the statements made by Greek Cypriot 
authorities following the killing of Yeoryiadhis has caused 
shock and amazement. He noted that those who know Turkey are 
well aware that it is against any manifestation of terror, 
whatever the reason. Ataman added that it is the responsibility 
of those who make such provocative allegations -- the goals 
which they serve being very clear -- to prove them. 
  In reply to a question, Ataman described the conclusion of a 
series of military cooperation agreements during the sudden 
visit by the Greek defense minister to south Cyprus as goals and 
intentions that threaten stability. 

</TEXT>

