<H3> <TI>   Demirel Statement Before Leaving for Romania </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2303115794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2303115794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] In an airport statement before 
leaving for Romania today, President Suleyman Demirel said: 
  [Begin recording] As you know, significant activity can be 
discerned in Turkish-Romanian economic relations. The number of 
Turkish entrepreneurs investing in Romania has recently been 
increasing and currently stands at 2,500. During our visit, we 
will also inaugurate a Turkish-Romanian bank. I would also like 
to announce that the number of mutual tourist visits between the 
two countries has exceeded 1 million in recent years. 
  Moreover, the existing problems and new developments in the 
Balkans as well as in the Caucasus and the Middle East make it 
imperative for Turkey and Romania, two important countries of 
the region, to hold more frequent contacts at every level. The 
restructuring of Europe also makes these contacts necessary. 
[end recording] 
  Demirel explained that ways to developing relations with 
regard to bilateral and international issues will be discussed 
during the visit. The president added that the possible 
contributions by Turkey and Romania to peace, stability, and 
cooperation in the region will also be reviewed. 
  Demirel was seen off at Ankara's Esenboga Airport by 
Husamettin Cindoruk, speaker of the Turkish Grand National 
Assembly. General Dogan Gures, chief of the General Staff, and 
other officials were also present. Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin also left for Romania together with the president. 

</TEXT>

