<H3> <TI>   Court Rejects Air France Case Against Airline Purchase </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403104594 Paris AFP in English 1040 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2403104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Luxembourg, March 24 (AFP) -- The European Court of 
Justice turned down a complaint from Air France here Thursday 
[24 March] that the British Airways purchase of the airline Dan 
Air might have breached European Union competition rules. 
  The Court turned down Air France's claim that the purchase 
of 
Dan Air in 1992 should have been investigated by the EU 
competition authorities. 
  The Court said Dan Air's turnover was not big enough to 
trigger an anti-trust investigation. 
  The European Commission approved the purchase last year 
after 
ruling that the resultant merger would not produce unfair 
competition for the Belgian airline Sabena. 

</TEXT>

