Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Wahn (DPA) -- The final 200 German blue helmet 
soldiers arrived home on Wednesday [23 March] from their 
humanitarian mission in the East African country of Somalia. 
They landed at the military section of the Cologne/Bonn Airport 
aboard two German Air Force aircraft. 
  They will be officially welcomed this afternoon by Defense 
Minister Volker Ruehe, of the Christian Democratic Union. The 
minister will then put the "German Somalia Support Union" out of 
service after a 10-month mission. 

