<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Continues Security Operations </TI></H3>
<H4>   Seize SAM's, RPG Launchers </H4>
<F P=102> TA2503154994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1525 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2503154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Mar 25 (AA) -- Two surface-to-air-missiles 
(SAM) were found in a hide-out belonging to separatist 
terrorists on Mount Agri (Ararat). 
  Security forces on an operation around the mountain in 
eastern Turkey found a hide-out. Two SAM's were found at the 
hide-out at the 13,000-foot (4,000 m) level. 
  Specialists say that the missiles were being used against 
aerial targets. 
  The same hide-out contained an RPG-type missile launcher, 27 
missiles, 43 rounds, 21 explosion moulds, a machine gun and a 
great number of Kalashnikov bullets, medicine and documents. 
  In an exclusive interview, Interior Minister Nahit Mentese 
confirmed the operation and said that security forces have been 
carrying out intensive operations since March 4 in Kars, Igdir 
and Agri. 
  `The importance of these operations are quite clear when you 
consider the damage which could have been done by the SAM's,' 
Mentese said. 
  Mentese also called on the terrorists to surrender. 
  `Let them surrender,' he said. `They have epidemics and 
instead of dying on the mountains let them surrender to the 
Turkish justice and benefit of the penitence law,' he said. 
  The SAM's have a 2-mile (3.6-km) range. The 20-pound (9-kg) 
missiles are manufactured by Russia and China. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-20003 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu058_q_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-058 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  25 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Continues Security Operations </TI></H3>
<H4>   Kill 11 `Terrorists' in Hizan </H4>
<F P=102> TA2503115394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1030 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2503115394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bitlis, Mar25 (A.A.) -- Eleven separatist 
terrorists have been killed in two-day clashes with security 
forces near Hizan township in the southeastern province of 
Bitlis, officials said on Friday [25 March]. 
  They told the Anatolian Agency that Thursday's death toll of 
four rose to 11 on Friday in continuing clashes. Two privates 
were also wounded. 
  Helicopters are taking part in the security forces' 
operation. 
  Over 11,000 people, including terrorists, members of 
security 
forces and civilians, have been killed in southeastern Turkey 
since 1984 when the separatists launched their bloody campaign 
for an independent state in the region. 

</TEXT>

