<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   2 Die, 10 Injured in Coffee House Raid </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2503114694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0910 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2503114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Mar. 25 (A.A.) -- Unidentified gunmen on 
Thursday [25 March] evening attacked a coffee house filled with 
supporters of pro-Islamic Prosperity Party (RP), killing two 
people and wounding 10, security officials said. 
  Four gunmen fired automatic weapons and threw hand grenades 
at the cafe in Istanbul's Kartal District on the city's 
outskirts, they said. 
  Supporters of the RP were holding a meeting at the time. 
  There were no immediate claims of responsibility. 
  There have been similar attacks on party offices throughout 
Turkey, where tension is running high before nationwide local 
elections Sunday. 

</TEXT>

