<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bursa, Mar 25 (AA) -- Five people were wounded in 
an armed clash in this northwestern city between the supporters 
of the True Path Party (DYP) and the Motherland Party (ANAP). 
  Additional security troops were sent to the Orhangazi 
township of Bursa, to quell the unrest. 
  The DYP is the main coalition partner and ANAP is the main 
opposition party. Both parties are conservative parties and are 
competing for the March 27 local elections. 

