<H3> <TI>   Deputy Foreign Minister on Talks in Washington </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2403221094 Athens ET-1 Television Network in Greek 2130 
GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2403221094 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ET-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Deputy Foreign Minister Yeoryios Papandreou is in 
Washington, where he had a meeting with high-ranking officials 
of U.S. President Bill Clinton's administration and members of 
Congress. 
  [Begin recording] [Papandreou] It was a very important 
meeting with members of the National Security Council and State 
Department. We discussed a series of issues, such as 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and developments in the Bosnian crisis, and 
had the opportunity to discuss issues of interest to both 
countries, including Cyprus, Greek-Turkish relations, The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia [FYROM], and other general 
European issues. All our contacts are on our national issues, 
including FYROM. 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Reportedly, Papandreou will 
inform the American officials of the Greek Government's answer 
and positive reply to Cyrus Vance's ideas on FYROM. According 
to Washington circles, the U.S. President's special coordinator 
is in continuous contact with UN mediator Cyrus Vance and is 
expected to visit Greece and FYROM soon. [passage omitted] [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

