<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Commissioner Arrives on Official Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2403202494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in English 1800 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2403202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The European Union's [EU] Commissioner for Foreign 
Affairs, Hans van den Broek, arrived in Cyprus this evening for 
talks with the government. The meetings will deal with Cyprus' 
entry into the Union, developments on the Cyprus problem, and 
the settlement of the fourth Cyprus-EU financial protocol. Van 
den Broek was accompanied by the EU observer on Cyprus, Serge 
Abou. 
  The two men will be honored at a dinner given by President 
Glavkos Kliridhis tonight. Tomorrow, they will meet with the 
members of the Foreign Ministry and with Foreign Minister Alekos 
Mikhailidhis. They will then have talks with President 
Kliridhis, Gustave Feissel [the UN secretary general's alternate 
special representative in Cyprus], and the ambassadors of the 12 
EU member states before leaving tomorrow afternoon. 

</TEXT>

