<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Stresses Heightened Interest </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2503040894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 2000 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2503040894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Hans van den Broek, European Union [EU] 
Commissioner on Foreign Affairs will have important talks on the 
Cyprus issue and Cyprus' relations with the EU. Van den Broek 
arrived here this evening accompanied by Serge Abou, the EU 
observer on the Cyprus issue. 
  Speaking upon his arrival, van den Broek said the EU and 
Cyprus are working together for Cyprus' EU accession. He said 
the Cyprus issue is dragging on and expressed the hope that 
Cyprus will be reunited. He also said that the EU's interest in 
a Cyprus solution became more pointed with the appointment of an 
observer to the talks. Van den Broek expressed regret that the 
talks are going through a difficult phase, as he put it, and 
called on the side responsible to cooperate with the Cypriot 
Government and United Nations, amend its position on the 
confidence-building measures, and cooperate for a political 
settlement. 
  Welcoming the EU commissioner, Foreign Minister Alekos 
Mikhailidhis expressed his deep gratitude and stressed that van 
den Broek has contributed decisively to historic beginnings for 
Cyprus, adding that it is hoped things will reach a successful 
conclusion with Cyprus' accession to the EU. Mikhailidhis also 
said that the EU commissioner's presence in Cyprus is very 
important. It is, he added, a political message indicating the 
importance of Cyprus' upgraded relations with the EU. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

