<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish `Agents' Monitoring National Guard </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2503112594 Nicosia KHARAVYI in Greek 25 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC2503112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia KHARAVYI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by K.P.] </F>
  [Text] Turkish agents are moving freely in the free areas, 
monitoring every move of the National Guard. 
  This is the police's evaluation after discovering evidence 
in 
Athalassa Forest during the search for the motorcycle used in 
Theofilos Yeoryiadhis' murder. Specifically, the police found a 
blue and white cigarette package of the Harman brand, which had 
the initials of the pseudostate [Turkish Republic of Northern 
Cyprus] inscribed on it. There were 15 cigarettes inside the 
package, which was found near a National Guard military camp. 
  Police are examining the package, which is believed to 
belong 
to Turkish secret service agents who systematically watch every 
move to and from the military camps. 

</TEXT>

