<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Solana Regrets Colosio's Death </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2403115294 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2403115294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The death of [Mexican presidential candidate] Luis 
Donaldo Colosio was met with consternation, not only in Mexico 
but also abroad, where the White House was the first to condemn 
this assassination. In Spain, Foreign Minister Javier Solana 
said this morning in the Congress of Deputies that he regretted 
this death. 
  [Begin Solana recording] I am shaken. When I got the news -- 
at 0500, when the Spanish ambassador in Mexico called me -- I 
was really dismayed, first of all, because of the loss of a very 
worthy man whom I had met and appreciated, and then because of 
what this means for Mexico from a political point of view. 
Mexico is a brother country, a country with whom we have so 
many relations. That is why I am shaken. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

