<H3> <TI>   Discusses Trade With Aho </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2503115594 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1100 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2503115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Free trade between Finland and the Czech Republic 
will not end even if Finland becomes a member of the EU 
[European Union]. The Czechs have been concerned that the 
KEVSOS [expansion unknown] agreement between Finland and the 
Eastern European countries would not be valid if Finland joined 
the EU. 
  Czech Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus, who is visiting Finland, 
and Finnish Prime Minister Esko Aho held talks on trade between 
the two countries in the morning. According to Finland, the 
ending of the KEVSOS agreement can be replaced with agreements 
between the EU and the Czech Republic if Finland joins the EU. 

</TEXT>

