<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ahtisaari Receives Croatian Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2403120694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1100 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2403120694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari received Mate 
Granic, Croatian deputy prime minister and minister of foreign 
affairs in the presidential palace in Helsinki today. Zdenka 
Kardum reporting from Helsinki: 
  [Kardum] Finland has been intensely following all 
developments in Croatia and Bosnia-Herzegovina. It has been 
present in the area through its international peace negotiators 
and its UNPROFOR [UN Protection Force] units in Croatia and 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. After the signing of the Washington 
agreement, Finland for the first time deems there is a 
possibility to restore peace in Croatia and Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  This was stated following talks with Finnish President 
Ahtisaari in the presidential palace in Helsinki today by 
Granic. Granic described their talks -- which were held behind 
closed doors -- as interesting and open, stressing that the 
Finnish president was an expert on our area, as he was one of 
the negotiators at the international peace conference in Geneva. 
  Finland's share in sending humanitarian aid to Croatia has 
been considerable, and it is also ready to offer aid in the 
future, both in the humanitarian field and through the 
deployment of its UNPROFOR units. It is interested in 
comprehensive economic, scientific, and cultural cooperation 
with our country. Finnish President Ahtisaari has accepted an 
invitation from Croatian President Franjo Tudjman to visit our 
country. 
  Granic also had talks today with his Finnish counterpart 
Heikki Haavisto. Haavisto also accepted Granic's invitation to 
visit Croatia, on which occasion the two ministers are to sign 
agreements on economic, scientific, technical, and cultural 
cooperation. 
  The Croatian foreign minister has also met the chairman of 
the foreign affairs committee of the Finnish parliament and is 
expected to meet the Finnish parliament speaker in the course of 
the afternoon. 

</TEXT>

