<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis: Turkish Cypriot Reply `Negative' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2503124094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1130 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2503124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis said the Turkish side 
has given a reply on the confidence-building measures that he 
described as negative. He added that the five UN Security 
Council permanent members have asked the UN secretary general to 
brief them on each side's positions. 
  Kliridhis made this statement while replying to reporters' 
questions at a luncheon for Greek Independence Day hosted by 
Greek Ambassador to Nicosia Alexandros Sandhis. Asked whether 
there is any possibility that the proximity talks will continue 
until 29 March, Kliridhis said there is very little leeway. He 
added that he believes the UN secretary general should proceed 
in preparing his report on the conclusion of the proximity talks 
and submit it to the Security Council. 
  After today's parade marking the 25 March holiday, Kliridhis 
was asked to comment on the latest developments in the proximity 
talks. He said that both the Greek Cypriot side and the five UN 
Security Council permanent members have asked for an objective 
report that describes each side's stance. 

</TEXT>

