<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minor Damage Caused by Arson Attack on Synagogue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2503111294 Hamburg DPA in German 0754 GMT 25 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2503111294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Luebeck (DPA) -- Last night, unknown 
perpetrators carried out an arson attack on the synagogue in 
Luebeck. Since the fire was soon discovered and the 
fire-brigade was called, only minor damage was caused. The room 
where the divine services are held was not damaged. 
  Winfried Tabarelli, senior director of the Criminal 
Investigation Department for the South of Schleswig-Holstein, 
said at the scene that there had been no indications of an 
attack. It is impossible to guard every possible target of an 
attack around the clock. Nevertheless, the attack has to be 
rated as attempted murder, since six families live in the house, 
he said. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

