<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   FDP's Hoyer Criticizes Schoenhuber </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2803105594 Hamburg DPA in German 0905 GMT 28 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2803105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- In the view of Werner Hoyer, 
secretary general of the Free Democratic Party of Germany [FDP], 
Franz Schoenhuber, chairman of the right-wing extremist 
Republikaner, must "be stopped." Schoenhuber's 
"unscrupulousness" in choosing his words -- who called Ignatz 
Bubis, chairman of the Central Council of Jews in Germany, an 
"instigator of people," and after the attack on the synagogue in 
Luebeck -- is "extremely alarming," Hoyer said in Bonn on Monday 
[28 March]. What Schoenhuber says is the "intellectual breeding 
ground for those who throw Molotov cocktails into synagogues and 
tacitly accept the death of people as a result." 
  Hoyer and FRG Justice Minister Sabine 
Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger (FDP) called on the democratic 
forces in the FRG to categorically defend themselves against 
Schoenhuber's words and deeds. Hoyer admonished that words such 
as "instigator of people" addressed to "such an upright and 
prudent man" as Bubis must "arouse all parties before they cause 
irreparable damage." 
  "It has always been a speciality of the German rightists to 
be the perpetrators and to support murders and then present 
themselves as victims," Herta Daeubler-Gmelin, deputy chairwoman 
of the Social Democratic Party of Germany, said in an interview 
on Suedwestfunk radio in Baden-Baden. However, she hopes that 
there will be a judge in Germany who will finally put "this 
instigator" behind bars. 

</TEXT>

