<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Envoy Denies Torture, Execution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2503182494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2503182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Turkish Ambassador to Bonn Onur Oymen -- </F>
recorded] 
  [Text] We welcome the German Government plans, in the wake 
of recent regrettable incidents in Germany, to extradite to 
Turkey some of our citizens who have committed crimes here in 
Germany. We declare that we are ready to cooperate with the 
German authorities in this matter. 
  Allegations to the effect that those who will be extradited 
will be executed or tortured in Turkey consists entirely of the 
propaganda waged by extremist organizations. This is what we 
are explaining to the Germans. We are discussing these issues 
with various organs. Such a mechanism exists between the 
Foreign Ministries of both countries. We have a committee 
comprised of the under secretaries of the Foreign, Justice, and 
Interior Ministries. Moreover, we decided to set up a 
cooperation committee between the Turkish and German Justice 
Ministries. I believe that it will not be difficult to reach an 
agreement with Germany on these and similar issues. It is 
important to trust one another and I believe that this mutual 
trust exists. 

</TEXT>

