<H3> <TI>   Eurofighter 2000 Makes Maiden Flight </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2803082594 Munich ARD Television Network in German 2015 
GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU2803082594 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich ARD Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The prototype of the Eurofighter 2000 plane 
successfully made its first test flight. The one-seat combat 
plane, the follow-up model of the disputed Fighter 90, is 
extremely maneuverable and can reach almost twice the speed of 
sound. According to Deutsche Aerospace, the unit price is to be 
no more than 100 million German marks. In addition to Deutsche 
Aerospace, British, Italian, and Spanish companies are also 
involved in the development of Eurofighter 2000. 

</TEXT>

