<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Czech Prime Minister on EU Membership Prospects </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2503152794 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1400 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2503152794 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Czech Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus hopes that his 
country's membership of the European Union [EU] will become a 
reality after Finland's membership. Klaus, who is visiting 
Finland, has held talks with political leaders about Finland's 
attitude toward the EU, among other things. On the basis of 
these talks, Prime Minister Klaus described Finland's attitude 
toward EU membership as an investment. 
  [Begin Klaus recording, in English] Finland definitely 
discovered that EC membership, this is now my terminology and 
not the terminology of the Finnish prime minister or anybody 
else, that EC membership is an investment. [end recording] 
  Klaus said that EU membership is not a miraculous cure but 
an 
investment that has its costs and its benefits. Positive and 
negative sides might appear at different stages and influence 
different parts of society in different ways, the Czech prime 
minister said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

