<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll: Growing Support for Opposition Parties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2603101494 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
0600 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2603101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the latest opinion poll, support for 
the Social Democratic Party [SDP] has risen to a record-high 
level during this election period. In an opinion poll carried 
out by Finnish Gallup for HELSINGIN SANOMAT, support for the SDP 
is about 34 percent. Support for the party is 12 percent higher 
than the number of votes it received in the last parliamentary 
elections. According to the opinion poll, the main government 
parties -- the National Coalition Party and the Center Party -- 
would both receive support of just under 18 percent. Joint 
support for the four government parties is now 43 percent. The 
opposition thus has a clear majority of support from the voters. 
Support for the Leftist Alliance was 11 percent, and support for 
the Greens has dropped to 6 percent. Support for the Finnish 
Rural Party has dropped to almost nothing. Last week, 2,000 
Finns were interviewed for the opinion poll. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

