<F P=101> Norway </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian Diplomat Expelled for Unsuitable Activities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2703135394 Oslo Radio Norway International in English 1300 
GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2703135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Oslo Radio Norway International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] An Iranian diplomat has been expelled by the 
Norwegian Foreign Ministry for so-called activities unsuited to 
his diplomatic status. Iran's ambassador was informed of the 
decision on Friday 25 March. Press spokesman Invard Havnen, in 
the Foreign Ministry, said that the deportation has nothing to 
do with the assassination attempt on William Nygaard, Norwegian 
publisher of Salman Rushdie's book, Satanic Verses. The Iranian 
diplomat has 10 days in which to leave Norway. 

</TEXT>

