<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Norway </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oslo, Nairobi Resume Diplomatic Relations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2703134894 Oslo Radio Norway International in English 1300 
GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2703134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Oslo Radio Norway International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Norway and Kenya have reopened diplomatic 
relations. Kenya closed Norway's embassy in Nairobi in 1990 
after Norway offered legal assistance to the Kenyan dissident, 
Koigi Wa Wamwere, who was under arrest at the time in Kenya. 
Norway had also criticized the human rights situation in Kenya. 
Kenya took the initiative in restoring diplomatic relations 
between the two countries. 
  Norway has no plans to restart economic aid to Kenya. 

</TEXT>

