<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Papandreou `Amazed' at Turkish Troops in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2503134894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1230 GMT 25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2503134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] After the conclusion of the military parade marking 
the anniversary of Greek Independence Day, Prime Minister 
Andreas Papandreou was asked to comment on the dispatch of 
Turkish troops to Bosnia-Herzegovina. He said: I am amazed 
that an army that invaded and occupied the northern part of 
Cyprus may be used for peacekeeping forces. It is amazing. 
  Asked about today's parade, Papandreou said: It was a 
perfect parade. Our Armed Forces are a strong force for 
safeguarding our country's integrity and defending peace. 

</TEXT>

