<H3> <TI>   Turkish Aircraft Violate Aegean Airspace 25 March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2603102194 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1000 GMT 26 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2603102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] There was a Turkish provocation on the day of our 
national holiday [25 March]. According to reports, yesterday 
morning when the military parade was taking place in Athens, 
about 20 Turkish F-16 and F-4 fighter aircraft entered the 
central Aegean without any previous notice, thus violating our 
national airspace and infringing on the rules of air traffic. 
Greek aircraft took off immediately and hastened to intercept 
the Turkish aircraft. 

</TEXT>

