Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Responding to a journalist's question on the 
Turkish violations yesterday, government spokesman Evangelos 
Venizelos said: 
  Yesterday, on the day of our national holiday, there was 
really an organized Turkish provocation, with the infringement 
of air traffic regulations and violations of the Greek airspace. 
The Turkish aircraft were spotted and intercepted by the Greek 
Air Force. 
  It is obvious that certain circles in Turkey want to create 
and cultivate a climate of tension. I wonder what they are 
after. Could it be that these acts are expedient for internal 
political reasons? 

