<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Election Turnout Figures Lower Than 1992 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2703215994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 2137 GMT 
27 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2703215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At the end of the first day of voting, the 
percentage of Italians who have voted in the Chamber of Deputies 
election was as follows: The national average was 57.3 percent 
compared with 67.6 percent for the general election in 1992. 
  The percentage details for the geographical areas were: 
  North -- 1994: 64.1 percent, 1992: 72.8 percent 
  Center -- 1994: 59.5 percent, 1992: 69.5 percent 
  South -- 1994: 47.6 percent, 1992: 60.1 percent 
  Islands -- 1994: 47.5 percent, 1992: 59.4 percent 

</TEXT>

