<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on 27 Mar Nationwide Local Elections </TI></H3>
<H4>   Polls Close Without Incidents </H4>
<F P=102> TA2703151994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 27 Mar 93 </F>
<F P=103> TA2703151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Mar. 27 (A.A.) -- Voting has ended in 31 
eastern and southeastern provinces and the counting of votes has 
begun. 
  Polling stations were closed at 4 p.m. In Adiyaman, Agri, 
Artvin, Bingol, Bitlis, Diyarbakir, Elazig, Erzincan, Erzurum, 
Gaziantep, Giresun, Gumushane, Hakkari, Kars, Malatya, 
Kahramanmaras, Mardin, Mus, Ordu, Rize, Siirt, Sivas, Trabzon, 
Tunceli, Sanliurfa, Van, Bayburt, Batman, Sirnak, Ardahan and 
Igdir. 
  Regional Emergency Governor Unal Erkan said during the 
voting 
that no important election-jeopardizing incident has occured in 
the region. 
  The Office of the Governorate organized a helicopter-tour in 
the region's villages for members of the foreign press who came 
to the site to cover the polls. 
  Erkan told the Anatolian Agency that 96 foreign journalists 
were in Diyarbakir. 
  "The majority of foreigners were conditioned to witness 
great 
unrest in the region," Erkan said. "They expected to see 
freedoms curbed, clashes erupting and security forces having 
difficulty in providing security." 
  Erkan said that the voter turnout was high. 

</TEXT>

