<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gunman Killed in Mersin; Election-Related Clash </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2703093994 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0905 GMT 27 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2703093994 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mersin, Mar 26, (AA) -- A gunman was killed and a 
policeman was wounded in an overnight election-related clash in 
this southern city, police said on Saturday [26 March]. 
  The clash started when gunmen, fleeing after throwing a bomb 
at the election office of the pro-Islamic Welfare [Prosperity] 
Party, fired on police, who urged them to surrender. One of the 
gunmen was killed, the others fled. 
  Five other people, including a 12-year-old boy, were killed 
and 26 were wounded in the last couple of days in several 
assaults on party offices and candidates in the run-up to 
Sunday's nationwide municipal elections. 

</TEXT>

