<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Justice Council Fails To Agree on Extradition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2603171594 Athens ATHENS NEWS in English 25 Mar 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> NC2603171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ATHENS NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The European Justice Council has made no progress on 
drawing up common rules on extradition because most EU [European 
Union] states are reluctant to surrender their own nationals to 
another state. Discussion also stumbled over whether political 
offences should be a motive for refusing extradition, a view 
that was not shared by Greece. "All (EU) member states have a 
democratic regime and live in a democratic atmosphere...it's not 
normal, therefore, that you should invoke political reasons," 
Greek Justice Minister Yeoryios Kouvelakis told reporters in 
Brussels. 

</TEXT>

