<H3> <TI>   Three Dutchmen Kidnapped in Yemen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2803123994 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1130 GMT 
28 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2803123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Three Dutchmen have been kidnapped in Yemen, the 
Dutch Foreign Ministry has confirmed. The three worked on a 
drinking water project and were seized last Friday [25 March] 
close to the capital, Sanaa. Nothing has been heard from them 
since. 
  The kidnapping is related probably to conflicts between 
local 
tribes and the government. Yemeni tribes regularly resort to 
kidnapping to add force to their grievances against the 
government. It is not known which tribe is responsible for the 
latest kidnapping. 

</TEXT>

