<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arms Found in Romanian Truck at Austrian Border </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2803184294 Vienna ORF Teletext in German 1636 GMT 28 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2803184294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna ORF Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Romanian truck that was stopped at the Suben 
superhighway checkpoint carried 2,300 (!) firearms. 
  "Wooden boxes" was tersely written on the declaration of 
goods that the driver presented. However, the German customs 
officers became suspicious and had a closer look at the 166 
boxes. They contained carbines, guns, machine guns, 
semiautomatic guns, ammunition, and parts of weapons. 
  The destination would have been a commercial firm in North 
Rhine-Westphalia. The freight was confiscated and criminal 
proceedings were instituted against the "receiver" and the truck 
driver. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

